metadata.description: Unique identifier for each opportunity record.
Indicates whether the opportunity has been deleted; represented as an integer.
Identifier for the account associated with the opportunity.
Indicates whether the opportunity is private; represented as an integer.
The name of the opportunity; Represents the title or identifier of the sales opportunity.
A brief overview of the opportunity; Provides context or details about the sales opportunity.
Current stage of the sales opportunity; Indicates the progress of the opportunity in the sales pipeline.
Numerical order of the stage in the sales process; Used to determine the sequence of stages in the sales pipeline.
Total monetary value of the opportunity; Represents the potential revenue from the sale.
Likelihood of closing the opportunity; Expressed as a percentage indicating the chance of winning the deal.
Projected revenue from the opportunity; Calculated based on the Amount and Probability.
Total quantity of items associated with the opportunity; Represents the number of units involved in the deal.
The date and time when the opportunity is expected to close; Format is ISO 8601.
Type of the opportunity; Indicates the nature of the sales opportunity.
The next action to be taken in the sales process for the opportunity.
Source from which the lead originated; Indicates how the opportunity was generated.
Indicates whether the opportunity is closed; Values are 0 for open and 1 for closed.
Indicates whether the opportunity was won; Values are 0 for lost and 1 for won.
Category of the opportunity for forecasting purposes; Includes values like Pipeline, Closed, etc.
Descriptive name of the forecast category for the opportunity.
Identifier for the marketing campaign associated with the opportunity.
Indicates whether the opportunity has associated line items.
Identifier for the price book associated with the opportunity.
Identifier for the user or team responsible for managing the opportunity.
Date and time when the opportunity was created; Timestamp indicating the creation moment.
Identifier of the user who created the opportunity; Unique ID for the creator.
Date and time when the opportunity was last modified; Timestamp indicating the last update.
Identifier of the user who last modified the opportunity; Unique ID for the last updater.
Timestamp indicating the last time the record was modified in the system.
Date of the most recent activity related to the opportunity.
Date when the opportunity's stage was last changed.
The fiscal year in which the opportunity is recorded, represented as a four-digit year.
The fiscal quarter during which the opportunity is recorded; Indicates the quarter of the financial year.
Unique identifier for the contact associated with the opportunity.
Identifier for the primary partner account linked to the opportunity.
Identifier for the contract associated with the opportunity.
Identifier for the last history record that tracks changes to the opportunity amount.
Identifier for the last history record that tracks changes to the opportunity close date.
Status of delivery and installation for the opportunity; Indicates the current state of delivery.
Tracking number associated with the opportunity; Used for monitoring shipment status.
Unique identifier for the order associated with the opportunity.
Type of generators currently being offered in the opportunity.
Key competitors involved in the opportunity.
Unique identifier for each account in the system.
Indicates whether the account has been marked as deleted.
Identifier for the master record associated with the account.
The name of the account.
Classification of the account, such as Customer or Partner.
Identifier for the parent account associated with this account.
Street address for billing purposes.
City where the billing address is located.
State associated with the billing address.
Postal code for the billing address.
Country where the billing address is located.
Geographical latitude of the billing address.
Geographical longitude of the billing address.
Accuracy level of the geocoding for the billing address.
Street address for shipping; includes details of the street name and number.
City where the account's shipping address is located.
State where the account's shipping address is located.
Postal code for the account's shipping address.
Country where the account's shipping address is located.
Latitude coordinate of the account's shipping address.
Longitude of the shipping address; Indicates the geographical longitude for shipping purposes.
Accuracy of the geocoding for the shipping address; Indicates the precision of the location data.
Primary contact phone number for the account; Used for customer communication.
Fax number associated with the account; Provides an alternative method for communication.
Unique identifier assigned to the account; Used for tracking and reference purposes.
The official website of the account; Provides a URL for more information about the company.
Standard Industrial Classification code; A numerical code that categorizes the account's industry.
Type of industry the account operates in; Describes the sector of business.
Total revenue generated by the account in a year; Measured in long integer format.
Total number of employees working for the account; Indicates the size of the company.
Type of ownership of the account; Indicates whether the account is Public, Private, or other classifications.
Stock ticker symbol associated with the account; Represents the company's stock in the market.
Detailed description of the account; Provides insights into the company's operations and offerings.
Current rating of the account; Indicates the quality or status of the account, such as Hot, Warm, or Cold.
Website URL of the account; Provides the online presence of the company.
Identifier for the user or entity that owns the account.
Timestamp indicating when the account was created.
Identifier for the user who created the account.
Timestamp indicating when the account was last modified.
Identifier for the user who last modified the account.
Timestamp indicating the last time the record was modified in the system.
Date of the last recorded activity associated with the account.
Identifier for the Jigsaw company record, used for data enrichment.
Unique identifier for the company in the Jigsaw database.
Status indicating the cleanliness of the account data, reflecting its accuracy and completeness.
Source from which the account was acquired; Indicates how the account was generated.
Dun & Bradstreet number assigned to the account; A unique identifier for business entities.
The trade name under which the account operates; Represents the brand name used in the market.
North American Industry Classification System code; Identifies the primary industry of the account.
Description of the industry associated with the NAICS code; Provides a textual representation of the industry.
Year when the company was established.
Description of the Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) code that categorizes the business.
Unique identifier assigned to the company by Dun & Bradstreet.
Identifier for the operating hours of the business.
Priority level assigned to the customer, indicating their importance to the business.
Service Level Agreement status; Indicates the level of service commitment provided to the account.
Flag indicating whether the account is currently active.
Total number of locations associated with the account.
Potential for upselling additional products or services to the account.
Unique serial number associated with the Service Level Agreement for tracking purposes.
The date and time when the Service Level Agreement (SLA) expires; Format is in ISO 8601.
